h the tech advocacy group fwdus in their efforts to advocate for comprehensive immigration reform he referred to the growing collaboration between silicon valley leaders and immigrant activists as a marriage of unlikely allies that bodes well for the passage of reform facebook founder and ceo mark zuckerberg who generally maintains a low public profile spoke before the screening of documented to introduce vargas and to lobby house members to keep up reform momentum zuckerberg recounted his experience tutoring undocumented students as his inspiration for starting fwdus in november 0 vargas served on the panel of judges for the dreamer hackathon hosted by fwdus at linkedin headquarters he was joined by zuckerberg dropbox ceo drew houston former groupon ceo andrew mason linkedin founder reid hoffman and fwdus president joe green the hour hackathon brought together undocumented immigrants and silicon valley tech veterans to create immigration reform advocacy projects the panel selected pushreform a web application developed by a team of dreamers to connect supporters to congress as the winning advocacy tool on july  0 vargas was arrested by immigration authorities while trying to leave the border town of mcallen texas vargas was there for a vigil organized by united we dream outside a shelter for recently released central american migrants he had a camera crew from define american with him to interview and film undocumented immigrant minor children from central america vargas later wrote that he did not realize until he was there that he would have to cross through a us customs and border protection checkpoint in order to leave the rio grande valley he went through airport security with his philippine passport and a pocketsize copy of the united states constitution initially he was cleared by the transportation security administration but a border agent took his passport reviewed his documents asked him some questions placed him in handcuffs and escorted him to the mcallen border patrol station for further questioning he was released later that day a statement followed that the release was because he had no history of criminal activity pen center usa announced in july 0 that they are giving vargas their 0 freedom to write award for immigration advocacy in his writing0 referencesedit  our team defineamerican 0 retrieved february  0   a b c breaking news reporting the pulitzer prizes pulitzerorg retrieved june  0   a b c d e f g vargas jose antonio my life as an undocumented immigrant the new york times june  0 accessed june  0  a b vargas jose antonio june  0 jose antonio vargas life as an undocumented immigrant time retrieved june  0   a b berestein rojas leslie june  0 jose antonio vargas im an american i just dont have the right papers scprorg retrieved february  0   a b ilustre jennie l jose antonio vargas pulitzer prize winner gma news online april 0  accessed june  0  a b c d from mv to dc pulitzer prizewinning mountain view alumnus chats with mentor los altos online october   retrieved june  0   a b younjoo sang february  0 jose antonio vargas calls for immigration reform michigan daily retrieved march  0   a b senate judiciary committee testimony jose antonio vargas pdf united states senate february  0 retrieved february  0   wilkesedrington lindsay 00 jose antonio vargas on john mccain gay undocumented journalist criticizes senators immigration stance video the huffington post retrieved 00   a b blogs are yesterday now its vlog time thewashingtoniancom washingtoniancom retrieved june  0   vargas jose antonio september   on wikipedia debating  hopefuls every facet the washington post retrieved march  0   jose antonio vargas work archived from the original on april  0 retrieved 00   students make connections at a time of total disconnect pulitzerorg april   retrieved june  0   pop poppop students down doors barred leaps to safety pulitzerorg april   retrieved june  0   that was the desk i chose to die under pulitzerorg april